episodes.title: One Planet
episodes.plot: Witness the planet's breathtaking diversity -- from seabirds carpet-bombing the ocean to wildebeests eluding the wild dogs of the Serengeti.

episodes.title: Frozen Worlds
episodes.plot: On the unforgiving frontier of climate change, polar bears, walruses, seals and penguins find their icy Edens in peril.

episodes.title: Jungles
episodes.plot: Jungles and rainforests are home to an incredible variety of species like preening birds, intelligent orangutans and remarkably ambitious ants.

episodes.title: Coastal Seas
episodes.plot: From fearsome sharks to lowly urchins, 90 percent of marine creatures live in coastal waters. Protecting these habitats is a battle humanity must win.

episodes.title: From Deserts to Grasslands
episodes.plot: Cameras follow desert elephants seeking sustenance, bison roaming North American grasslands and caterpillars living the good life underground.

episodes.title: The High Seas
episodes.plot: Venture into the deep, dark and desolate oceans that are home to an abundance of beautiful - and downright strange - creatures.

episodes.title: Fresh Water
episodes.plot: The need for fresh water is as strong as ever. However, the supply is becoming increasingly unpredictable for all manner of species.

episodes.title: Forests
episodes.plot: Examine the fragile interdependence that exists between forests' wide variety of residents, including bald eagles, hunting dogs and Siberian tigers.
